title: ICE: 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', compiler/rustc_middle/src/hir/map/mod.rs:180:30

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
I got this bug deep in the middle of trying things (abstracting some code of `sqlx`'s `Executor` trait, similarly to https://github.com/eaze/tide-sqlx/blob/latest/src/lib.rs). My codebase at this time is a big work-in-progress mess so I won't post it now, but I saved it. The bug is reproducible, and I can give you more information if needed! ### Code ```Rust use async_trait::async_trait; #[async_trait] trait My<'tx> { async fn get_conn(&'tx mut self) -> api::Result where E: Executor<'tx>; //#[tracing::instrument] pub async fn save_tmp(&self, session_id: &[u8], ip: &str, expiration: i64, field: &str, data: &[u8]) -> api::Result<()> { sqlx::query("replace into `tmp` values (?, INET_ATON(?), FROM_UNIXTIME(?), ?, ?)") .bind(session_id) .bind(ip) .bind(expiration) .bind(field) .bind(data) .execute(todo!()).await.map_err(|e| api::Error::ServerSideError(e.into()))?; Ok(()) } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.52.0-nightly (caca2121f 2021-03-05) binary: rustc commit-hash: caca2121ffe4cb47d8ea2d9469c493995f57e0b5 commit-date: 2021-03-05 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.52.0-nightly LLVM version: 12.0.0 and rustc 1.52.0-nightly (8f349be27 2021-03-08) binary: rustc commit-hash: 8f349be27815d43d462a32faeb270a22a68486b6 commit-date: 2021-03-08 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.52.0-nightly LLVM version: 12.0.0 ```
